A camera operator at a Hungarian television station has been caught on camera kicking and tripping running Syrian refugees. Ana Kasparian (The Point), and John Iadarola (Think Tank), hosts of the The Young Turks, break it down. Tell us what you think in the comment section below.

\"They say reporters shouldn’t try to make themselves part of the story, but perhaps someone should have told the camera crews.

A photographer, reportedly working for Hungarian news station N1TV, was caught on camera tripping a Syrian refugee who was trying to escape from the police in the village of Röszke. The refugee was carrying a child at the time.”*

